                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1239">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/335.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Miller</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 16, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your July 12. Exchange quotes in New York July 11, 3225, July 13, 32, July 14th,
                    3150. Department can obtain exchange rate from New York and telegraph it at
                    regular intervals. How often would you suggest? Will port authorities accept
                    rate thus quoted?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
